article.headline: MVSU 22, Savannah St. 20
article.story: ITTA BENA, Miss. -- Paul Roberts scored three touchdowns, including the game-winner with five seconds left in the game, to help Mississippi Valley State come from behind to beat Savannah State 22-20 on Saturday. Roberts completed 20 of 37 passes for 252 yards with two touchdowns and two interceptions, adding 15 yards and a touchdown on 12 carries for the Delta Devils (2-4). Paul Cox, who caught the game-winning 4-yard touchdown pass, had 84 yards and two touchdowns on six receptions. Kurvin Curry threw for 173 yards with one touchdown and rushed for 79 yards for the Tigers (3-5). After Savannah State's Derek Williams hit a 24-yard field goal to open the scoring, Roberts hit Cox for an 18-yard score and Zack Gilarski's 39-yard field goal gave the Delta Devils a 9-3 lead at the close of the first. Rashard Russell ran for an 8-yard score, and Williams' 23-yard field goal put the Tigers back on top 13-9 at halftime. After a scoreless third quarter, Roberts ran for a 1-yard score that was matched by a 20-yard touchdown connection between Curry and Deleon Hollinger that gave the Tigers a 20-16 lead with 36 seconds to play. But, 31 seconds later, Roberts threw his final touchdown pass to Cox for the victory.
